  <prompt>Collapse the TWO `Meter("Sprk.Bff.Api.Cache")` instances (today at `TenantCache.cs:28-32` static fields + `Telemetry/CacheMetrics.cs:25-40`) into a SINGLE canonical `Sprk.Bff.Api.Telemetry.CacheMetrics` STATIC class owning the Meter + all instruments. Remove the `CacheMetrics?` constructor injection from every consumer (`EmbeddingCache`, `GraphTokenCache`, plus 1-3 others via grep). Static class means: no DI registration; consumers call `CacheMetrics.RecordHit(...)` etc directly. Apply ¬ßF.1 static-scan to ensure no asymmetric registration regression. Apply ¬ßF.2 Fixture-Config-FIRST if WAF-based test fixtures regress.</prompt>
  <role>Senior .NET developer with OpenTelemetry Metrics + DI minimalism (ADR-010) experience. Apply `task-execute` skill at FULL rigor. Apply `bff-extensions.md` ¬ßF.1 + ¬ßF.2.</role>
  <goal>Exactly ONE Meter instance `Sprk.Bff.Api.Cache` at runtime (verified by task 005). `Sprk.Bff.Api.Telemetry.CacheMetrics` is a `static class` owning the Meter + instruments. Zero references to `CacheMetrics` as an INSTANCE type (no `ICacheMetrics`, no `CacheMetrics?` ctor injection). All consumers call static methods. Build clean; tests at baseline.</goal>
  <context>
    <background>Spec FR-02: today two Meters are created independently (TenantCache static fields + CacheMetrics instance class), claiming the same name. OTel will emit metrics from BOTH, doubling counts or causing unstable behavior. Cause: R1 created CacheMetrics in task 041 (instance class for DI) AND R1 task 006 added static Meter fields directly on TenantCache. R2 unifies.</background>
