  <steps>
    <step order="1">Grep audit ‚Äî find ALL CacheMetrics consumers + ALL Meter("Sprk.Bff.Api.Cache") creators. Commands: `grep -rn "CacheMetrics" src/server/api/` + `grep -rn 'Meter("Sprk.Bff.Api.Cache")' src/`.</step>
    <step order="2">Read CacheMetrics.cs current implementation. Note constructor + instance fields. Plan promotion: instance fields ‚Üí static readonly; constructor ‚Üí static initializer; instance methods ‚Üí static methods.</step>
    <step order="3">Promote `CacheMetrics` to `public static class CacheMetrics`. Static Meter + static Counters + static Histograms. Static methods `RecordHit`, `RecordMiss`, `RecordDuration`, `RecordFailure` (Failure added in task 001 if not landed yet ‚Äî coordinate).</step>
    <step order="4">Remove static Meter + Counter fields from TenantCache.cs lines ~28-32. Replace any `s_hits.Add(...)` calls with `CacheMetrics.RecordHit(...)`.</step>
    <step order="5">Remove `CacheMetrics?` constructor parameter from EmbeddingCache, GraphTokenCache, plus any others found in step 1. Convert `_metrics?.Record(...)` ‚Üí `CacheMetrics.Record(...)`.</step>
    <step order="6">Remove CacheMetrics DI registration from CacheModule.cs (or wherever registered). Verify no `AddSingleton&lt;CacheMetrics&gt;` remains.</step>
    <step order="7">¬ßF.1 static-scan: confirm no asymmetric registration. Static class has no DI registration ‚Äî no symmetry concern (which is the point of static).</step>
    <step order="8">Build: `dotnet build src/server/api/Sprk.Bff.Api/` ‚Äî 0 errors.</step>
    <step order="9">Run BFF unit tests `dotnet test --filter "FullyQualifiedName~Sprk.Bff.Api"`. ¬ßF.2: if WAF fixtures break, inspect fixture config FIRST (DI minimalism + static class may surface latent fixture issues).</step>
